Description: Almost complete clay seal-impression bearing one seal impression of an oval scarab-like seal. The rear of the sealing shows three rows of basketry coil on one side and on the other side one row of basketry coil as well as several string impressions of a non-twisted string. The seal itself shows a seated mAa.t-figure with a feather in the hair and an ankh on the knees, facing to the left to the end of the seal. Behind the figure a standing falcon facing to the left. Behind the falcon an upright uraeus. Same motif as on EA86678. A lot of finger impressions next to the seal.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
